4. Consider an application which when it runs sequentially takes 20 minutes to complete while 80% of its execution can be parallelized. 
   How long will it take when it runs on 16 processors?
----------------------------
Parallelization Speedup Sequential time=20 minutes | 80% can be parallelized, 20% must be sequential
Use Amdahl’s Law: Speedup= 1/(S+(1-S)/P). Where: S =0.2 and P = 16 | Speedup = 1/ (0.2+0.8/16)= 1/(0.2+0.05)= 1/0.25=4 |New time = 20/4= 5 minutes
